claim.claim-text:
1. A method of facilitating processing of a mobile-originated voice call for a mobile station attached with a femtocell system, comprising:
receiving, by the femtocell system, a call origination request from the mobile station;
in response to receiving the call origination request, transmitting, by the femtocell system, authentication data in a service request message to a convergence server deployed in a core network;
receiving, by the femtocell system, a global challenge response from the convergence server in response to sending the authentication data, wherein the global challenge response includes an authentication token that is stored at the femtocell for subsequent transmission from the femtocell back to the convergence server; and
receiving, by the femtocell system, a determination of validation for the voice call from the convergence server.

8. A non-transitory computer-readable medium having computer-executable instructions tangibly embodied thereon for execution by a processing system, the computer-executable instructions for facilitating processing of a mobile-originated voice call for a mobile station attached with a femtocell system that, when executed, cause the processing system to:
notify, by the femtocell system, the mobile station that authentication is required by the mobile station for system access;
receive, by the femtocell system, a call origination request from the mobile station;
in response to receiving the call origination request, transmit, by the femtocell system, authentication data in a service request message to a convergence server deployed in a core network;
receive, by the femtocell system, a global challenge response from the convergence server in response to sending the authentication data, wherein the global challenge response includes an authentication token that is stored at the femtocell for subsequent transmission from the femtocell back to the convergence server; and
receive, by the femtocell system, a determination of validation for the voice call from the convergence server.
